  "texts": [
    "Knowledge is physically unobservable and has no fundamental units.",
    "That is why we use indicators or proxies.",
    "Reliance on these proxies is not necessarily bad.",
    "As an example, the amount of money that a firm spends on research for new products is reasonably well-defined and economically meaningful.",
    "But because it is a step away from the fundamental inputs to the innovation process, its use in empirical research always raises issues of interpretation that may cloud our understanding of what we are observing."
  ],
